threat_severity.level_description: Severity MEDIUM because it was considered trojan.

crowdsourced_yara_results.description: Detects a suspicious ELF binary with UPX compression
crowdsourced_yara_results.author: Florian Roth (Nextron Systems)

attributes.magic: ELF 32-bit MSB executable, MIPS, MIPS-I version 1 (SYSV), statically linked, no section header

crowdsourced_ai_results.analysis: This MIPS-based ELF binary is identified as a malicious botnet agent, likely a variant of Mirai or Mozi. It is packed using UPX (indicated by 'upx.sf.net' and the characteristic decompression logic in '_start'). The presence of exploitation paths such as 'POST /GponForm/diag_' indicates targeting of GPON router vulnerabilities (CVE-2018-10561). Functional analysis shows suspicious memory manipulation via 'sys_mmap' and 'sys_mprotect' in 'sub_4208fc' to execute unpacked code, and persistence-related strings involving '/proc/self/exe' and '/tmp'.
